explains: adv. 敏锐地；强烈地；锐利地

sentences.en: He observes keenly, but says little.
sentences.cn: 他观察敏锐，但言语寥寥。

sentences.en: She remained keenly interested in international affairs.
sentences.cn: 她一直对国际事务有强烈的兴趣。

sentences.en: They're keenly aware that whatever they decide will set a precedent.
sentences.cn: 他们敏锐地意识到无论他们决定怎么做，都会开创先例。
